Commands:
    create_logic_tests:

    create_logic_tests is used to create stored pattern logic tests for
    the device under test.


create_logic_tests:

 [-H]                                  Help Text
 [-h]                                  Help Text
 [-ALTFAULT <string>]                  Use Alternate Fault Model
  -EXPERIMENT <string>                 Experiment Name
 [-INEXPERIMENT <string>]              Input Experiment Name
 [-LINEHOLD <infilename>]              Linehold File
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
  -TESTMODE <string>                   Test Mode Name
  -WORKDIR <string>                    Working Directory
 [-aliascheck no|yes] (no)             Check for fault aliasing on designs with XOR compression
 [-allowconstraintsimthroughmuxselpin yes|no] (yes) Allow constraint simulator to propagate constraint through MUX select pin
 [-append no|yes] (no)                 Append to Existing Experiment
 [-balancehierblockcoverage <decimal 0.00 to 100.00>[,<decimal 0.00 to 100.00>]...] Minimum Test Coverage (approximate)
 [-bsuboptionsfile <string>]           File containing options for bsub command - when there's white space in options
 [-checkpoint <integer 0 or greater>]  Checkpoint Interval in minutes (approximate)
 [-choppers safe|risky] (Conditional Default) Clock Chopper Simulation
 [-constraintcheck no|yes] (yes)       Detect Run-Time Constraint Violations.
 [-contentionremove hard|soft|allx|none] (hard) Type of Three-state Contention to Remove
 [-countxcaptureswitches half|no|yes] (half) Count X transitions as switching activity
 [-domaincutoff <decimal>]             Domain Cutoff Percentage
 [-effort low|high] (high)             Test Generation Effort
 [-faulttype static|staticbridge[,static|staticbridge]...] (static) Limit Faults to Selected Type
 [-fromexperiment <string>]            Experiment From Which to Map Fault Status (exists in fromtestmode)
 [-fromtestmode <string>]              Testmode for Experiment from which to Map Fault Status
 [-globalterm 0|zero|1|one|either|both|none] (Conditional Default) Tester Provided Termination on Product Drivers
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-hiercaptureswitching <integer 0 to 100>] Specifies the maximum percentage of switching allowed on a hierblock during capture
 [-holdcgoverrides yes|no] (Conditional Default) Apply automatic lineholds for clock gate overrides identified during low power ATPG
 [-holdflopoverrides no|yes] (no)      Apply flop lineholds for clock gate overrides identified during low power ATPG
 [-hosts <string>]                     Host Machines for Parallel Processing
 [-ignoremeasures <infilename>]        Ignore Measures File
 [-includesysclkforhalfcycleconstraint yes|no] (yes) Allow constraint simulator to use system clocks on latch to determine half cycle constraints.
 [-keepers safe|risky|no] (Conditional Default) Keeper Device Simulation
 [-latchsimulation optimistic|pessimistic] (optimistic) Sim Latch/Flip-flop Output to X when Clock at X
 [-logmode append|overwrite] (overwrite) Specify the mode of writing to logfile : append or overwrite.
 [-maxcaptureswitching <integer 0 to 100>[,<integer 0 to 100>]...] Specifies the maximum percentage of switching allowed on any pulse during capture
 [-maxcarebits <integer 0 to 255>]     Maximum Care Bits Per Cycle
 [-maxcoverage <decimal 0.00 to 100.00>] Maximum Adjusted Test Coverage (approximate)
 [-maxcputime <decimal>]               Maximum CPU Minutes (approximate)
 [-maxelapsedtime <decimal>]           Maximum Elapsed Minutes (approximate)
 [-maxfaultsize <integer>] (Conditional Default) Maximum Fault Size
 [-maxglobalcoverage <decimal 0.00 to 100.00>] Maximum Global Adjusted Test Coverage (approximate)
 [-maxpatterns <integer>]              Maximum Number of Patterns (approximate)
 [-maxscanswitching <integer 5 to 100>[,<integer 5 to 100>]...] Specify the Maximum Percentage of Switching Allowed During Scan
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-messagesuppressionfile <infilename>]File containing messages that needs to be filtered
 [-messagesuppressionrc include|exclude] (include) Option to exclude return code of the command based on the highest severity code of suppressed messages
 [-multiclockcompaction yes|no|only]   Multi Clock Compaction
 [-ndetect <integer 2 to 65534>]       Allow the fault to be detected for the specified number of times in test patterns before marking it tested
 [-nonscanlatch latch|flush|buffer] (latch) Treat non-scan pipeline latches as latches, or flush latches
 [-numprocesses <integer 2 to 63>]     Number of Slaves in Parallel Processing
 [-numslaves <integer 2 to 63>]        Number of Slaves in Parallel Processing
 [-pdl <integer>:] (0)                 Possible Detect Limit - 0 for No Limit
 [-pistimswhileclkon yes|no] (no)      Allow PI Stimulus while Clocks are ON during Sequential Test Generation
 [-postprocessconstraintsiminparallel yes|no] (yes) post process constraint simulation results in parallel to identify violation.
 [-propxignore no|yes] (Conditional Default) Propagate X to Downstream Logic from Ignored Location
 [-queuename <string>]                 Queue name for LSF utility
 [-ramsimulation optimistic|pessimistic] (optimistic) Sim RAM instance Output to X when write port of that primitive at X
 [-ramsize all|<integer>:] (all)       RAM Address Space Size
 [-removexlatch no|yes]                For compression. Remove patterns which have Latch=X.
 [-removexpo no|yes] (Conditional Default) For Compression. Remove Patterns Which Have PO=X.
 [-reportclockgateinfo compact|all] (compact) Report Information About Clock Gates in the Design
 [-reportfaultsummary yes|no] (no)     Report Fault Summary
 [-reportheartbeat <integer 0 or greater>] (60) Report Heartbeat Interval since the last Sim Report or Heartbeat (minutes)
 [-reportsequencefaults yes|no|run] (no) Report Test Sequence Fault List Size
 [-reportsequences yes|no] (no)        Report Test Sequences
 [-restart no|yes|end]                 Restart from Checkpoint
 [-sequencefile <infilename>]          Sequence File Name
 [-sequentialdepth <integer 0 to 32>]  Maximum Sequential Depth the Test Generator is Allowed to Try
 [-setupsequence <string>[,<string>]...] (Global Data Default) Setup Sequence
 [-simpatterns yes|no|all] (yes)       Simulate Patterns
 [-singleload no|yes]                  Single Load
 [-singletimeonly no|yes]              Create single time tests
 [-stimclock yes|no] (no)              Allow Clocks to be Stimmed (as well as pulsed)
 [-testscan yes|no] (Conditional Default) Create Scan Test Patterns
 [-testsequence <string>]              User Test Sequences
 [-tgfaultlist <infilename>]           List of fault indexes the test generator will target
 [-writemasksall yes|no]               Add Mask Events to all Test_Sequences
 [-writepatterns yes|no|all] (yes)     Write Patterns to TBDbin
 [-xmask no|yes] (yes)                 For compression. Perform Channel Masking.

