 [-h]                                  Help Text
 [-DESIGNSOURCE <string>]              Design Source File(s)
 [-EXPORTDIR <outdir>]                 Directory to Contain Export Data (default is part directory)
 [-INEXPERIMENT <string>[,<string>]...]Name(s) of InExperiment(s)
 [-LOG no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to Log
 [-LOGCOMPRESS yes|no] (no)            Compress the log file
 [-LOGFILE <outfilename>]              Write to specified log file
 [-STDOUT no|all|summary|nosummary] (all) Customize Data Written to STDOUT
 [-TECHLIB <string>]                   Technology Cell Definition File(s)
  -TESTMODE <string>                   Test Mode Name
  -WORKDIR <string>                    Working Directory
 [-bidipins drivez|measurex|mask] (Conditional Default) Set how non controlling BIDIs will be treated
 [-capturebidioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic capture timing - Set the default capture BIDI offset
 [-captureperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic capture timing - Set the capture period
 [-capturepioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic capture timing - Set the default capture PI offset
 [-capturepioffsetlist <string>]       Set the individual dynamic capture PI offsets
 [-capturepioffsetlistfile <infilename>] File containing individual dynamic capture PI offsets
 [-capturepulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic capture clock pulse width
 [-capturepulsewidthlist <string>]     Set the individual dynamic capture clock pulse widths
 [-capturepulsewidthlistfile <infilename>] File containing individual dynamic capture clock pulse widths
 [-capturestrobeoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic capture timing - Set the capture strobe offset (measure)
 [-capturestrobetype window|edge] (edge) Global dynamic capture timing - Set the capture strobe type
 [-capturetimeunits ps|ns|us|ms] (ns)  Global dynamic capture timing - Set the capture time units
 [-clockinitialstate previous|down|up|no] (previous) Specify the initial state of clock.
 [-combinesections no|yes|all] (no)    Limit the number of output files.
 [-compressfiles no|yes] (Conditional Default) Compress the resulting vector files
 [-compresspatterns yes|no] (no)       Compress test vectors across pattern boundaries
 [-dataformat binary|hex] (binary)     Format for the STIL output data
 [-dutname <string>]                   Changes the default design under test name (dut) for verilog
 [-explicitshifts <integer 1 or greater>] (1) Allows the user to supply the number of explicit scan shifts required when doing parallel verilog simulation.
 [-help <string>]                      Help Facility
 [-includealldynamictimeplates yes|no] (no) Include all dynamic timeplates or only the timeplates that are used.
 [-includelatchnames no|yes] (no)      Include latch/flop name in scan out miscompare messages
 [-includemodeinit yes|no|separate|limit|only|include|all|includeall] (Conditional Default) How to handle the modeinit sequence in the output vector files. Values other than yes or include must be used with caution.
 [-includeopcgcsls yes|no] (no)        Include first correlated opcg in case representative opcg flop is in pseudoblock.
 [-includepinnames no|yes] (no)        Include pin name in scan out miscompare messages
 [-initbidioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global modeinit timing - Set the default modeinit BIDI offset
 [-initperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global modeinit timing - Set the modeinit period
 [-initpioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global modeinit timing - Set the default modeinit PI offset
 [-initpioffsetlist <string>]          Set the individual modeinit PI offsets
 [-initpioffsetlistfile <infilename>]  File containing individual modeinit PI offsets
 [-initpulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global modeinit pulse width
 [-initpulsewidthlist <string>]        Set the individual modeinit clock pulse widths
 [-initpulsewidthlistfile <infilename>]File containing individual modeinit clock pulse widths
 [-initstrobeoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global modeinit timing - Set the modeinit strobe offset (measure)
 [-initstrobetype window|edge]         Global modeinit timing - Set the modeinit strobe type
 [-inittimeunits ps|ns|us|ms]          Global modeinit timing - Set the modeinit time units
 [-language stil|verilog|wgl|tdl|verilog_hw] (verilog) Specify the language in which to write vectors
 [-latchnametype primitive|cell] (primitive) Specify the type of the latch name to be printed.
 [-latchreleaseoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Set the offset when the latches should be released for parallel Verilog
 [-limitcomments no|yes|passthru] (no) Limit commentary in the output vectors.
 [-limittimeplates no|yes] (Conditional Default) Limit timeplates to one for scan/test.
 [-logmode append|overwrite] (overwrite) Specify the mode of writing to logfile : append or overwrite.
 [-maxsequencesperfile <integer 1 or greater>] Specify the maximum number of test sequences allowed in any one output vector file
 [-messagecount <string>]              Limit Messages for Specified Message Id (e.g., messagecount=XXX-710=3).
 [-messagecounteach <integer>]         Default Limit for Each Message.
 [-messagecounteachseverity all|excludeinfo] (all) Level of severity for which messages are to be suppressed as per messagecounteach
 [-messagesuppressionfile <infilename>]File containing messages that needs to be filtered
 [-messagesuppressionrc include|exclude] (include) Option to exclude return code of the command based on the highest severity code of suppressed messages
 [-misrobserve parallel|serial] (parallel) Set how to observe the MISR values
 [-misrperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global misr timing - Set the misr period
 [-misrpioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global misr timing - Set the default misr PI offset
 [-misrpioffsetlist <string>]          Set the individual misr PI offsets
 [-misrpioffsetlistfile <infilename>]  File containing individual misr PI offsets
 [-misrpulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global misr pulse width
 [-misrpulsewidthlist <string>]        Set the individual misr clock pulse widths
 [-misrpulsewidthlistfile <infilename>]File containing individual misr clock pulse widths
 [-misrstrobeoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global misr timing - Set the strobe offset (measure)
 [-misrtimeunits ps|ns|us|ms]          Global misr timing - Set the misr time units
 [-modeinitfilename <string>]          Change the default modeinit output file name, based on this name
 [-modeinitsequenceonly no|yes] (no)   Enable writing modeinit sequence in verilog, tdl, stil and wgl after build_testmode and without creating any ATPG patterns.
 [-modeinittimingfile <infilename>]    File containing modeinit timing
 [-modulealias <string>]               Set the Verilog module alias name
 [-mospins <string>]                   Set the MOS pins.  Example mospins=pi1,pi2,etc
 [-mosstates <string>]                 Set the MOS states and cores associated with that state.  Example mosstates=001=core1,010=core2,etc
 [-multibitscanshifts no|yes] (no)     Support multiple shifts in a scan chain library cell if needed.
 [-multipintracing no|yes] (yes)       Trace all the pins on scan path to identify stim points for scan flop 
 [-outputfilename <string>]            Change the default output files name, based on this name
 [-outputmainsim yes|no|all] (yes)     Create the mainsim file containing definition and tasks
 [-outputvectors yes|no] (yes)         Create the pattern/data file containing input and output values
 [-parallelshifts <integer 1 or greater>] (1) Allows the user to supply a number of dummy scan shifts after normal parallel scan.
 [-pinasdata <string>]                 Specify a pin or a list of pins to be treated as a data pin
 [-pinorder <infilename>]              File containing pin ordering information
 [-printlatchfailures no|yes] (no)     Print detailed latch failure information for all latches.
 [-pulseclockcharacter default|edge] (default) Pulse clock character to be used for clocks
 [-pulsestart priorvalue|offvalue] (priorvalue) Set whether pulse's should start waveforms/timeplates with the previous value or the off value
 [-releasebidioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic release timing - Set the default release BIDI offset
 [-releaseperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic release timing - Set the release period
 [-releasepioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic release timing - Set the default release PI offset
 [-releasepioffsetlist <string>]       Set the individual dynamic release PI offsets
 [-releasepioffsetlistfile <infilename>] File containing individual dynamic release PI offsets
 [-releasepulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global dynamic release clock pulse width
 [-releasepulsewidthlist <string>]     Set the individual dynamic release clock pulse widths
 [-releasepulsewidthlistfile <infilename>] File containing individual dynamic release clock pulse widths
 [-releasetimeunits ps|ns|us|ms] (ns)  Global dynamic release timing - Set the release time units
 [-renamecapture <string>] (CAPTURE)   Change the default CAPTURE name for timeplate
 [-renameinit <string>]                Change the default init timeplate name
 [-renamerelease <string>] (RELEASE)   Change the default RELEASE name for timeplate
 [-renamescan <string>]                Change the default scan timeplate name
 [-renametest <string>]                Change the default test timeplate name
 [-repeatheartbeat <integer 0 or greater>] (1000) Enable Verilog simulation heartbeat messages in a repeat loop
 [-reportbsvportmap no|yes] (no)       Dump file contain the mapping between tester cycle and associated chip port for Boundary Scan Failure Analysis
 [-scanbidioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global scan timing - Set the default scan BIDI offset
 [-scanbidipins drivez|measurex|mask] (Conditional Default) Set how non controlling BIDIs will be treated during scan
 [-scanformat serial|parallel] (Conditional Default) Set the scan format
 [-scanperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global scan timing - Set the scan period
 [-scanpioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global scan timing - Set the default scan PI offset
 [-scanpioffsetlist <string>]          Set the individual scan PI offsets
 [-scanpioffsetlistfile <infilename>]  File containing individual scan PI offsets
 [-scanpulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global scan pulse width
 [-scanpulsewidthlist <string>]        Set the individual scan clock pulse widths
 [-scanpulsewidthlistfile <infilename>]File containing individual scan clock pulse widths
 [-scansetuptiming default|test] (default) Timeplate to be used for scan setup operations
 [-scanstrobeoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global scan timing - Set the strobe offset (measure)
 [-scanstrobetype window|edge]         Global scan timing - Set the scan strobe type
 [-scantimeunits ps|ns|us|ms]          Global scan timing - Set the scan time units
 [-sdfname <string>]                   SDF Filename(s)
 [-setpaddingpatterns <decimal 0 or greater>] (0) Set the number of padding patterns
 [-signalsfile yes|no] (yes)           Create a file containing common elements (signals)
 [-signalsfilename <string>]           Change the default signals output file name, based on this name
 [-stimclock yes|no] (Conditional Default) Specify if stimming a clock to its ON state is allowed
 [-temporaryfilelocation tmp|exportdir] (tmp) Specify the directory for creating temporary outputs files.
 [-testbidioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global test timing - Set the default test BIDI offset
 [-testperiod <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global test timing - Set the test period
 [-testpioffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global test timing - Set the default test PI offset
 [-testpioffsetlist <string>]          Set the individual test PI offsets
 [-testpioffsetlistfile <infilename>]  File containing individual test PI offsets
 [-testpulsewidth <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global test timing - Set the test pulse width
 [-testpulsewidthlist <string>]        Set the individual test clock pulse widths
 [-testpulsewidthlistfile <infilename>]File containing individual test clock pulse widths
 [-testrange <odometerRange>]          Select Range of Tests
 [-testrangefile <infilename>]         File containing Range of Tests
 [-testsectiontype all|burnin|channelscan|iddq|logic|logiclbist|scan|path[,all|burnin|channelscan|iddq|logic|logiclbist|scan|path]...] (all) Print specific Test Sections only.
 [-testsequence <string>]              Specify a sequence or a list of sequences to be included in the output vectors.
 [-teststrobeoffset <decimal 0.000000 or greater>] Global test timing - Set the test strobe offset (measure)
 [-teststrobeoffsetlist <string>]      Set the individual test Strobe offsets
 [-teststrobetype window|edge]         Global test timing - Set the test strobe type
 [-testtimeunits ps|ns|us|ms]          Global test timing - Set the test time units
 [-timingfile <infilename>|no]         File containing scan, test or init timing keywords
 [-verilogformat fullnetlists|reducednetlists] (fullnetlists) Full or Reduced Verilog Netlists to be used for Verilog Simulation
 [-waitcycleafterchannelmaskexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the channel mask scan exit sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterchannelmaskprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the channel mask scan preconditioning sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterdiagreturn <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the diagnostic observation return sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterdynamic <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after a dynamic timed pattern has been processed
 [-waitcycleafterlowpowergatingenable <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the low power gating scan enable sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterlowpowergatingexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the low power gating scan exit sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterlowpowergatingprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the low power gating scan preconditioning sequence has been applied
 [-waitcycleaftermisrobserve <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the MO pins are measured in the MISR Observe Sequence
 [-waitcycleaftermodeinit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the mode initialization sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafteropcgexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the opcg scan exit sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafteropcgprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the opcg scan preconditioning sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterpreset <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the resetable pipelines and elastic register sequence has been applied
 [-waitcycleafterscanexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the Scan Exit Sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleafterscanprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the Scan Preconditioning Sequence has completed
 [-waitcycleaftersigobsreturn <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the signature observation return sequence has completed
 [-waitcyclebeforechannelmaskexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the channel mask scan exit sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforechannelmaskload <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the channel mask load sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforechannelmaskprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the channel mask scan preconditioning sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforediagobserve <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the diagnostic observation observe sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforedynamic <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before a dynamic timed pattern has been processed
 [-waitcyclebeforelowpowergatingenable <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the low power gating scan enable sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforelowpowergatingexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the low power gating scan exit sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforelowpowergatingload <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the low power gating scan load sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforelowpowergatingprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles after the low power gating scan preconditioning sequence has completed
 [-waitcyclebeforemeasurepo <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before any static measure PO
 [-waitcyclebeforemisrobserve <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the MO pins are measured in the MISR Observe Sequence
 [-waitcyclebeforeopcgexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the opcg scan exit sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforeopcgload <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the opcg scan sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforeopcgprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the opcg scan preconditioning sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforescanexit <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the Scan Exit Sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforescanload <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the Scan Load Sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforescanprecon <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the Scan Preconditioning Sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforesigobsobserve <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before the signature observation observe sequence has been applied
 [-waitcyclebeforestaticpulse <integer 0 or greater>] Wait X number of cycles before any static clock pulse

@modus:root:/ 12> exit
